						<div class="postbody">Looking (and sounding) good, rainwarrior.  Few things I found, albeit minor:<br /><br />- Main NSFplug UI has a window title of &quot;NSFplug&quot; (lowercase &quot;p&quot;), while rest of the program uses &quot;NSFPlug&quot; (capital &quot;p&quot;)<br />- Configuration area with General/APU1/APU2/etc. tabs has a window title of &quot;NSFPlug&quot;; I'd strongly suggest &quot;NSFPlug - Settings&quot;<br />- Some pixel adjustments need to be made to the UI configuration tabs' &quot;Options&quot; sections, to keep them looking consistent.  Boxes, spacing of the text/checkboxes, etc. are different between APU2 vs. FDS vs. APU1, etc.<br />- &quot;Default number of Loops&quot; lets you decrease the number all the way to 0 (which used to be permitted), but now trying to use a value of 0 throws an error dialog insisting the value must be between 1 and 256.  If 0 isn't supported any more, no problem -- make the spinner (up/down arrows) stop at 0<br /><br />If you upload the source somewhere I can fix these up/provide a diff, particularly for the layout/UI ones.</div>

