					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Wow! This is sounding amazing! Just one, seemingly minour point, and a compatibility problem with XmPlay. <br /><br />1. Would it be possible to have an option for the n163 that makes it behave like older emulators, where only 3 bits of the waveform are read, and not the full 6? This would be useful for older nsf's that rely on this behaviour. Personally, I'd rather patch the nsf's so that they play properly on the real hardware, but I think having the option in the player would be useful as a stopgap measure. Speaking of patching, could someone remind me, or point me to the entry where someone mentioned how to patch older n163 nsf files to sound right?<br /><br />2. Right now in XmPlay, I'm finding that switching songs, especially after a few switches leads to XmPlay crashing, or at least becoming unresponsive and causing windows 7, either 32 or 64-bits, to bring up it's this program is not responding... dialog. I can't seem to track down a consistent pattern to the behaviour, but when the dialogs do come up, what info should I get to try track down the bug? I haven't got winamp installed right now to test to see if it's XmPlay specific, or if it's something else causing the weirdness.<br /><br />thanks</div>

